explanation: The solution iterates through all possible factors of n. If a factor is found, it decrements the k counter. When k reaches 0, the current factor is returned as the kth factor. If the loop completes without finding the kth factor, -1 is returned.  This approach has a time complexity of O(n) in the worst case, as it might iterate through all numbers from 1 to n.

